    "last_edit_date" : 1524814309,
    "creation_date" : 1484235480,
    "answer_id" : 41617184,
    "question_id" : 38992114,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Idea 17eap: </p>\n\n<p><code>sout</code>: Prints </p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>soutm</code>:  Prints current class and method names to System.out</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(\"$CLASS_NAME$.$METHOD_NAME$\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>soutp</code>: Prints method parameter names and values to System.out</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println($FORMAT$);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>soutv</code>: Prints a value to System.out</p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(\"$EXPR_COPY$ = \" + $EXPR$);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6971999,
      "reputation" : 482,
      "user_id" : 5849332,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3197976b19fc222ba6c7516343f59703?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Leo",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5849332/leo"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 16,
    "last_activity_date" : 1509630074,
    "creation_date" : 1509630074,
    "answer_id" : 47076800,
    "question_id" : 38992114,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Open up Settings (By default is Alt + Ctrl + S) and search for Live Templates. In the upper part there's an option that says \"By default expand with TAB\" (TAB is the default), choose \"Custom\" and then hit \"change\" and add the keymap \"ctrl+spacebar\" to the option \"Expand Live Template/Emmet Abbreviation\".</p>\n\n<p>Now you can hit ctrl + spacebar and expand the live templates. Now, to change it to \"syso\" instead of \"sout\", in the Live Templates option, theres a list of tons of options checked, go to \"other\" and expand it, there you wil find \"sout\", just rename it to \"syso\" and hit aply.</p>\n\n<p>Hope this can help you.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9569453,
      "reputation" : 738,
      "user_id" : 7107573,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/141888713066099/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Vyas Ramankulangara",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7107573/vyas-ramankulangara"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 59,
    "last_activity_date" : 1597953349,
    "last_edit_date" : 1597953349,
    "creation_date" : 1510073985,
    "answer_id" : 47163482,
    "question_id" : 38992114,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want to know all the shortcut in intellij hit <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>J</kbd>. This shows all the shortcuts. For <code>System.out.println()</code> type <code>sout</code> and press <kbd>Tab</kbd>.</p>\n"
  }, {
